{
    "name": "Terra-Cotta Garrison",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Terra-Cotta Garrison",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Bestiary 3",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Bestiary 3 pg. 263",
                        "alt": "Bestiary 3 pg. 263",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq024xj"
                    },
                    "page": 263
                }
            ],
            "html": "These constructed warriors can work together as a trained group to repel intruders.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"563\" game-obj=\"Rules\">Recall Knowledge - Construct</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"2\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Arcana</a></u>, <u><a aonid=\"4\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Crafting</a></u>)</b>: DC 31<br/><b><u><a aonid=\"563\" game-obj=\"Rules\">Unspecific Lore</a></u></b>: DC 29<br/><b><u><a aonid=\"563\" game-obj=\"Rules\">Specific Lore</a></u></b>: DC 26"
        },
        {
            "name": "Terra-Cotta Warrior",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Runic Impressions",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Bestiary 3",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Bestiary 3 pg. 263",
                                "alt": "Bestiary 3 pg. 263",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq024xj"
                            },
                            "page": 263
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "advice_and_rules",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Advice and Rules",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Advice and Rules",
                        "image": "Sidebar_1_AdviceAndRules.png"
                    },
                    "html": "At its creation, a terra-cotta warrior can be engraved with runes as if it were a weapon with an item level equal to its creature level, applying these runes to the weapons it wields. Such runes can't be removed and engraved on items. The soldier here has only a <a aonid=\"281\" game-obj=\"Equipment\"><i>+1 weapon potency</i></a> rune and a <a aonid=\"280\" game-obj=\"Equipment\"><i>striking</i></a> rune, but more powerful versions with more powerful potency and property runes have been known to exist."
                }
            ],
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Bestiary 3",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Bestiary 3 pg. 263",
                        "alt": "Bestiary 3 pg. 263",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq024xj"
                    },
                    "page": 263
                }
            ],
            "html": "Terra-cotta warriors guard the tombs of ancient rulers, where they stand vigil, animating only when intruders break in to pilfer riches or defile the tomb itself. Each warrior is meticulously crafted from clay and given unique features."
        }
    ],
